{
  "version": 1,
  "name": "Capacitor Discharge Demo",
  "lesson": {
    "title": "Capacitor Discharge Demo",
    "description": "Hold the tact button to charge the 1000µF capacitor through the center 470Ω resistor. The cap and the east branch (470Ω + red LED) are in parallel. Release the button — USB disconnects, but the charged cap powers the LED through the east branch and it fades out over about 1–2 seconds as the cap empties. Orient the LED at 90° (anode north, cathode south). Put the cap + toward the power side."
  },
